item.title: Where is loader.java?
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461

@sk8rdude461 wrote:

[quote=“noah1gamble, post:9, topic:508929”][quote author=sk8rdude461 link=topic=627169.msg4262607#msg4262607 date=1363602856]

I Tried typing it in my search bar but nothing comes up, i cant even search for anything atm, so i just need to know where Loader.java is located?

Client sided somewhere…
I don’t know the structure of the folders in higher revision clients…

Im trying to get a 718 to work, but i just cant seem to get it, i used to be able to, but i forget, can yyou help? i start the server, then the client, it gets stuck on 0% and eventually jre_connect

Is the server online, before loading the client.

And by that you mean i ran the server? (Like this)
The base is NRS3 V4.

What else would I mean…
Yes…
The server needs to be fully online before you run the client.

Listen don’t get smart with me,It still does not work, i think it my cache.

My bad potato boy.

Your cache is is located in the server. The client needs to connect to the cache to work. 1 + 1 = 2. Get it?
[/quote]
LOL Child please, i don’t need to be talked down to by an 11 year old XD. Potato motherloveer. :)[/quote]
First of all, I’m 17. Second, you’re the person that posted a picture of himself, said potato, got butthurt when the community trolled you, and cried. Third, I guarantee I could code circles around you. Fourth, Ahram is 12 (or 11?) and he could code better than me; so check yourself.
